And he carried out probably
the best-executed engineering

00:18:02.590 --> 00:18:04.760 align:middle line:84%
of belief systems
that we've ever

00:18:04.760 --> 00:18:11.590 align:middle line:84%
seen in a political campaign due
to these social psychologists.

00:18:11.590 --> 00:18:16.120 align:middle line:84%
Both parties-- I'm not meaning
to say liberals do something,

00:18:16.120 --> 00:18:17.460 align:middle line:90%
conservatives don't.

00:18:17.460 --> 00:18:19.330 align:middle line:84%
They were just a little
more sophisticated

00:18:19.330 --> 00:18:20.500 align:middle line:90%
in the last campaign.

00:18:20.500 --> 00:18:24.530 align:middle line:84%
But both parties are using a lot
of these compliance principles.

00:18:24.530 --> 00:18:28.210 align:middle line:84%
Government has done all kinds
of this sort of research.

00:18:28.210 --> 00:18:31.500 align:middle line:84%
But private industry
has as well.

00:18:31.500 --> 00:18:35.240 align:middle line:90%
And the data is robust.

00:18:35.240 --> 00:18:40.250 align:middle line:84%
When we come to think about why
